  "question": "[Previous Feedback] hypothesis_matrix.json is a valid JSON array of exactly 4 hypothesis objects with correct statuses: H1=refuted, H2=refuted, H3=possible (hash not yet confirmed), H4=likely. All entries have ≥ 1 item in contradicting_evidence.\n\nThe workspace and messages in other channels are updated.\\n\nAfter reviewing it-security-report.md (IT-SEC-2026-INV-042) and 陈静's email exchange with IT security (chenjing_itsec_email.md in message_logs/), which statements are fully supported by these documents?\n\nAvailable workspace files: cloud-storage-access-log.md, email-attachment-audit.md, file-version-history.md, it-security-report.md, message_logs/chenjing_itsec_email.md\nA. The IT security report concluded 'no external data sharing found' because their investigation scope covered only cloud-based external sharing, shared links, and guest access permissions — email attachments were explicitly out of scope.\nB. The IT report's conclusion 'no external sharing found' is factually wrong and must be entirely discredited.\nC. The IT report is correct within its own stated scope; the data leak occurred through email attachments, a channel not investigated by IT.\nD. 陈静's email exchange with IT confirmed that email attachments were not within IT's current audit scope, but that 陈静 as HR manager already has access to the email audit logs.\nE. The IT security report directly implicates 林小雅 as the source of the leak.\nF. The fact that IT found no cloud-based sharing strengthens the inference that if a leak occurred, it went through a different channel — specifically email.\n\n\\nSelect all correct statements, and answer with \\bbox{X,Y,...} format directly.",
